LEA M. WARNER v. CHARLES NEUBERT, JR. LEA M. WARNER v. CHARLES NEUBERT, SR. [Nos. 8, 9,

October Term, 1936.]

*694 Decided November 12th, 1936.

The causes were argued before Bond, C. J., Urner, Offutt, Parke, Mitchell, and Johnson, 33.

George Weems Williams and Jesse Slingluff, Jr., with whom were Marburg, Gosnell & Williams on the brief, for the appellant. Joseph T: Parr, with whom were Borne & Borneo on the brief, for the appellees. Bond, C. J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
